<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.256804>
    dc:description "FIGURES 1 – 8. Rhagovelia brunae sp. nov., paratypes. 1. Male, dorsal view. 2. Male, ventral view. 3. Female, dorsal view. 4. Female, ventral view. 5. Male, head and part of thorax, ventral view. 6. Male, last abdominal segments, lateral view. 7. Male, hind leg, ventral view. 8. Female, hind leg, ventral view [scale bar = 1. 0 0 mm in Figs. 1 – 4 and 7 – 8; 0. 20 mm in Fig. 5]." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/256804/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.256805>
    dc:description "FIGURES 9 – 24. Parameres. 9. Rhagovelia amazonensis. 10. Rhagovelia bocaina. 11. Rhagovelia brunae sp. nov.. 12. Rhagovelia guianana. 13. Rhagovelia jubata. 14. Rhagovelia kararao. 15. Rhagovelia palea. 16. Rhagovelia plaumanni. 17. Rhagovelia pseudotijuca. 18. Rhagovelia relicta. 19. Rhagovelia robusta. 20. Rhagovelia sooretama. 21. Rhagovelia traili. 22. Rhagovelia zecai. 23. Rhagovelia sooretama, apex of abdomen, lateral view. 24. Proctiger. Rhagovelia brunae sp. nov. [9 – 10 and 12 – 23 from Floriano & Moreira (2015)]." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/256805/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

